With social media and constant social interaction being such a big part of our lives, it’s easy to get caught up in the noise and lose sight of what really matters.
It’s been so refreshing to take a step back a little and prioritize my time and energy. 
I encourage you all to try it out for yourselves. Take some time to disconnect from the digital world and reconnect with the people and activities that make your heart sing. Trust me, it’s worth it. ❤️ #mentalhealth #selfcare #priorities #focusonwhatmatters #grateful

May 2021 - ( before NFTs peak,
pre-AI ) we used Times Square Billboards to activate an early #augmentedreality version of my “Peace Makers” sculpture, while physically on display in Randalls Island Park NYC and at Taglialatella Galley NYC. 
I didn’t realize how multidisciplinary, intersectional, experimental and interactive it was. We were just having fun in doing it! 
Today I see this is exactly the direction #Art is shifting. Experimentation IS why I love making art!! This project was made with the incredible team of @madewithbrandxr and @cubeartfair

Posted @withregram • @randallsisland Planted by the 103rd Street Footbridge, Rubem Robierb’s Empower Flower, joyfully welcomed visitors to the park for the past year. We are saddened to say goodbye to this lovely sculpture which represents praise, unity and support of women’s rights.

Rubem Robierb is known for using strong symbolism and underlying messages in his artwork, which often centers around deep-rooted social issues such as LGBTQ+ Rights, women’s empowerment, immigration, climate change, and racism. The Empower Flower’s throne provided a unique space for visitors to become the central focus of the artwork. Thank you Rubem, for sharing this beautiful sculpture with the park and all of our patrons!

“Empower Flower” just ends its residency in Randalls Island Nyc.
Another incredible experience to have my art as part of people’s everyday lives…new projects coming.
Thank you @randallsisland @nycparks  and @taglialatellagalleries .

Posted @withregram • @samchampion I have HOPE .  Hope in a country my father served as a career @marines . Hope in a country where I have fought for equal rights.  Hope in a country where I legally married my husband. Hope in a country where I pursued an education and the career of my dreams.  I see hate and stupidity trying to “kill” this American experiment. I see the hate driven by greed in cooperation with powerful, foreign enemies… but ( because of my father) I believe good wins if we fight for it.  Happy Birthday America 🇺🇸
When we rise above divisions, embracing empathy and understanding, we unlock the true potential of society. 🇺🇸

Inspired in the FOREVER Stamps,
I created this piece/protest in 2017.
In the beginning of the extreme political division that has established in our country.
I thought after elections I could “return” the FOREVER word again to its original state.
I thought by now the worst would be past us.  In reality this division persists.
Every time a nonsense legislation maliciously targets our LGBTQA+community, women rights and other marginalized communities, we realize that our fight for Freedom, Equality, Liberty and Justice is far from over. Yet we are fighting and in many ways, winning.

No winner, no loser…Altinha” is a fight against gravity.  A fascinating ballet at the edge of the ocean.
People in Rio are obsessed with “Altinha” ; a beach game born during the 60’s in the sands of Ipanema beach. Practiced by the seaside by at least two people, the aim is simply to prevent a soccer ball from touching the ground by keeping it as high up in the air possible, which is also the origin of the name (“alto” means “high” in Portuguese). Despite it’s only requirement is a soccer ball, the game has little to do with soccer itself.  The participants play for each other and against nobody. “No hands” is the only rule.

As an artist it is rewarding when your work  reaches different audiences with its message of PEACE and RESPECT; despite our background, race, ethnicity or religion or gender.
This is desperately needed right now….LOVE YOUR NEIGHBOR AS YOURSELF ✌🏾!!

PEACExWAR - Part 1
The narrative of WarxPeace has been a constant subject in my work. In the conflict ofWar,  humanity disappears, lives are brutally taken and peace feels impossibly out of reach.  I often discuss opposing forces in my work. Whether it be Dark/light, Love/hate or War/peace…we often spend our lives immersed in the struggle of these differences… how to understand them… why they exist and how they intersect
#peace #coexist #humanity
“In the shadow of war’s devastation, there are no victors, only the bitter realization that we’ve all lost a piece of our shared humanity.”

With my HEart collection Im playing with the visual codes of  the heart symbol, juxtaposed with everyday phrases and signage, the HeART Series expresses the immediacy of today’s emotional conversations. Modern “feel it, say it, share it” society’s expressions are colorfully shared in whimsical, Large scale neon lighted canvases.

Rubem Robierb.

Investiga la identidad como premisa de la raza y su fuerza social en OHM. Los conceptos básicos de poder quedan demostrados en su obra Ring (2009), en la que se observa el código del dinero, el poder y la satisfacción del sexo. Este conjunto de ideas son el estímulo de su trabajo. La irruptora fotografía ampliada del empaque del preservativo XL se convierte en un impacto conceptual, donde el tamaño si importa. El empaque, que brilla bajo la medida del oro, es la fuente de poder.
